      <guid>https://edrictam.github.io/home/about/</guid>
      <description>Biography I am currently a PhD student in Statistics at Duke University and a graduate student in Applied Mathematics at Columbia University.
I am broadly interested in Bayesian Methodology and Statistical Machine Learning. I am also interested in their applications in Computational Biology, Medical Imaging, and Financial Econometrics.
Prior to Duke, I studied Computer Science at the University of Chicago, performing research at Booth&amp;rsquo;s Department of Econometrics and Statistics under the mentorship of Veronika Rockova.</description>
    </item>
    
